# Generate SSH Key
ssh-keygen -t rsa -b 4096 -f ~/.ssh/custom_key_name


# Copy and paste public key
sud cat ~/.ssh/custom_key_name.pub

# Add public key into bitbucket

# Add private key in KeyVault

# use the key as env variables in Jenkins pipeline and use it in checkout stage

NOTE: Use SSH url for checkout.
====
ðŸ”¹ Step 3: Retrieve SSH Private Key in Jenkins
Go to Manage Jenkins â†’ Configure System

Find the "Azure Key Vault" section

Click "Add KeyVault Secret"

Secret Name: GitHubSSHKey (same as stored in Key Vault)

Secret Type: SSH Private Key

Credential ID: GitHub-SSH-Key (note this for Jenkinsfile)

Click Save
-------------
pipeline {
    agent any
    stages {
        stage('Checkout Code') {
            steps {
                sshagent(['GitHub-SSH-Key']) {
                    sh 'git clone git@github.com:<your-username>/<repo-name>.git'
                }
            }
        }
    }
}
